00:16:39,690 --> 00:16:44,100
Xue Jiao, I never admitted it,
but I hid it from you because I was avoiding it.

269
00:16:46,464 --> 00:16:48,665
I should've told you about C1 earlier

270
00:16:48,665 --> 00:16:51,995
and let you know my plan.

271
00:16:53,020 --> 00:16:55,030
I should've

272
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:58,280
confessed everything to you
the day after you got drunk.

273
00:16:58,280 --> 00:16:59,758
Be honest.

274
00:16:59,758 --> 00:17:01,979
Also, last time, Lin Zhi Hua
did something bad to you.

275
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:03,640
It was also my fault.

276
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:06,480
I thought,
if I don't think about it or mention it,

277
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,430
I won't have to face it.

278
00:17:10,870 --> 00:17:12,640
That was wrong.

279
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:19,770
I'm sorry.

280
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:28,030
Honestly, I was running away too.

281
00:17:32,050 --> 00:17:35,910
It's not that I hated the old you.

282
00:17:35,910 --> 00:17:39,410
I hated the old me.

283
00:17:39,410 --> 00:17:41,490
But whenever I see you,

284
00:17:41,490 --> 00:17:43,630
I'm reminded of it.

285
00:17:44,390 --> 00:17:48,280
No matter how hard I try to erase that past,

286
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:50,420
it never goes away.

287
00:17:50,420 --> 00:17:52,520
Don't erase it.

288
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:54,722
Why would you do that?

289
00:17:54,722 --> 00:17:58,720
The you now and the you back then.

290
00:17:58,720 --> 00:18:01,700
Without either, you wouldn't be who you are today.

291
00:18:02,970 --> 00:18:05,010
If you really think that way,

292
00:18:05,010 --> 00:18:07,220
why did you keep it from me so long?

293
00:18:17,674 --> 00:18:19,454
Xue Jiao.

294
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,800
Xue...

295
00:18:32,759 --> 00:18:34,254
 Xue Jiao. 

296
00:18:34,254 --> 00:18:35,860
 Meet me at the company building. 

297
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:38,680
 The same place where
you were wronged last time. 

298
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:42,020
 Please, do come over. 

299
00:19:09,193 --> 00:19:11,453
 Safe travels. 

300
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:20,330
Babe...

301
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:54,460
What do you wanna say?

302
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,920
Do you remember this?

303
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:03,260
This is...

304
00:20:03,897 --> 00:20:07,547
The code you wrote to apply for the transfer.

305
00:20:08,093 --> 00:20:11,630
There is a critical bug in the code you wrote.

306
00:20:11,630 --> 00:20:13,040
No way.

307
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:15,040
I reviewed it many times.

308
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,920
Can you show me the error log?

309
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,940
Let me check where the problem is.

310
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:20,880
Of course, I remember.

311
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,530
- How would you...
- How would I also remember?

312
00:20:23,530 --> 00:20:25,340
Do you think I made a mistake?

313
00:20:25,340 --> 00:20:26,580
That's not what I meant.

314
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:28,950
Then what do you mean?

315
00:20:33,219 --> 00:20:35,049
Ms. Gu,

316
00:20:35,580 --> 00:20:39,360
we do take responsibility
for this recruitment mishap.

317
00:20:42,010 --> 00:20:43,720
Forget it.

318
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:45,660
I quit.

319
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:58,670
Actually, after you said "I quit" here,

320
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:01,442
I reviewed your code.

321
00:21:01,442 --> 00:21:03,970
So I know your style very well.

322
00:21:03,970 --> 00:21:06,380
After picking out the illogical parts,

323
00:21:06,380 --> 00:21:08,850
it's obvious it was your work.

324
00:21:09,722 --> 00:21:12,302
Also, after you gave it to Lin Jia Dong this time,

325
00:21:12,302 --> 00:21:17,180
he even tampered with the same part again.

326
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:23,250
Well, then, thank him for me.

327
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:26,220
I managed to rent this place before Xintu did.

328
00:21:29,180 --> 00:21:33,090
This will be our startup from now on.

329
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:45,820
Do you still remember what your app was about?

330
00:21:45,820 --> 00:21:47,260
What?

331
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:49,380
You wanna interview me again?

332
00:21:49,380 --> 00:21:50,810
No.

333
00:21:56,954 --> 00:21:59,332
You interview me.

334
00:21:59,332 --> 00:22:01,412
Don't mind if I do.

335
00:22:16,380 --> 00:22:18,330
Hello, everyone.

336
00:22:19,153 --> 00:22:23,943
Today, I'm here to introduce
a new in-car smart app.

337
00:22:24,791 --> 00:22:28,310
The inspiration came from her father.

338
00:22:28,310 --> 00:22:31,010
My father is a ride-hailing driver.

339
00:22:31,010 --> 00:22:32,660
To pick up a few more rides,

340
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:34,540
he leaves home early and works late.

341
00:22:34,540 --> 00:22:36,140
It has given him health issues.

342
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:37,790
His memory's bad too.

343
00:22:37,790 --> 00:22:42,830
He wonders if the car is locked
after he gets home.

344
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:45,364
From a business perspective,

345
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:48,840
designing an app for a small user group
may feel pointless.

346
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:52,580
But niche doesn't mean it should be ignored.

347
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:57,260
Niche doesn't mean it's invisible.

348
00:23:00,970 --> 00:23:04,260
Our C2 system in development is looking

349
00:23:04,260 --> 00:23:09,940
to include adaptive modes
like senior mode and special needs mode.

350
00:23:09,940 --> 00:23:11,960
 

351
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,840
Miss Gu Xue Jiao,

352
00:23:16,434 --> 00:23:19,684
would you be willing

353
00:23:19,684 --> 00:23:22,183
to license your app idea?

354
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,170
I...

355
00:23:32,827 --> 00:23:35,356
Last time,

356
00:23:35,356 --> 00:23:38,296
I missed the chance
to help you realize your idea.

357
00:23:41,029 --> 00:23:44,299
But I hope this time, you can give me that chance.

358
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:54,240
 

359
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,290
Likewise...

360
00:24:02,289 --> 00:24:07,920
 ♫ No more regrets ♫ 

361
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:09,940
Last time,

362
00:24:12,009 --> 00:24:13,969
I didn't hold on to you.

363
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:22,930
I also hope this time,

364
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:28,740
you can give me a chance.

365
00:24:30,830 --> 00:24:32,460
Then

366
00:24:33,123 --> 00:24:35,573
what's the time limit?

367
00:24:35,573 --> 00:24:37,767
Unlimited renewal.

368
00:24:37,767 --> 00:24:44,100
 ♫ I'll be yours through every turn of time ♫ 

369
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,570
Happy to work with you.

370
00:24:52,870 --> 00:24:54,820
Promise.

371
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:15,410
Sugar?

372
00:25:16,210 --> 00:25:18,820
One sugar cube, half a spoon of cocoa.

373
00:25:18,820 --> 00:25:22,270
Extra milk foam, 85°C water.

374
00:25:33,690 --> 00:25:39,250
I'll have a coffee corner in our startup space.

375
00:25:39,250 --> 00:25:41,980
You're set on renting that place?

376
00:25:43,325 --> 00:25:44,326
What?

377
00:25:44,326 --> 00:25:48,050
Did your bad memories give you PTSD of that place?

378
00:25:48,050 --> 00:25:49,820
Scared?

379
00:25:49,820 --> 00:25:53,650
I wouldn't say it's scary.

380
00:25:54,625 --> 00:25:56,450
I agree.

381
00:25:56,450 --> 00:26:00,300
The last Lin Zhi Hua wasn't that bad.

382
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:04,290
Except in the elevator, I was kinda harsh.

383
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:06,150
This is bad.

384
00:26:06,150 --> 00:26:08,220
Very bad.

385
00:26:09,040 --> 00:26:11,860
You've been watching me for this long.

386
00:26:11,860 --> 00:26:14,060
What are you up to?

387
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:17,050
I didn't even know you secretly checked my code

388
00:26:17,050 --> 00:26:20,200
for the transfer interview.

389
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:23,230
Seems like you cared a lot about our contractors.

390
00:26:25,342 --> 00:26:26,900
I've always wanted to explain about these.

391
00:26:26,900 --> 00:26:30,890
Just that I didn't get a chance.

392
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:33,860
That's just an excuse.

393
00:26:33,860 --> 00:26:36,483
You need to fight for a chance.

394
00:26:36,483 --> 00:26:38,050
You're right.

395
00:26:38,050 --> 00:26:41,630
I guess I didn't try hard enough.

396
00:26:43,170 --> 00:26:45,413
From now on, you just lift your finger.

397
00:26:45,413 --> 00:26:48,913
I'll go where you say. Sound good?

398
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:53,900
Then I need you to let go of me now.

399
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:55,500
No can do.

400
00:26:56,760 --> 00:27:00,330
What? You only hear what you wanna hear.

401
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:07,440
Okay.

402
00:27:08,550 --> 00:27:11,660
Well. Since you've been watching me for so long,

403
00:27:11,660 --> 00:27:13,765
and you know all about me,

404
00:27:13,765 --> 00:27:16,505
now it's my turn to know you.

405
00:27:17,110 --> 00:27:19,060
How many...

406
00:27:20,225 --> 00:27:23,296
ex-girlfriends?

407
00:27:23,296 --> 00:27:24,896
Me?

408
00:27:25,590 --> 00:27:27,580
You know my circle.

409
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:31,460
Always Gao Rui, Lin Jia Dong, Professor Tan.

410
00:27:32,232 --> 00:27:34,255
Unlike you.

411
00:27:34,255 --> 00:27:38,350
That ex-boyfriend of yours, Yi Tian Yu,
is still hanging around.

412
00:27:44,180 --> 00:27:47,190
Past crimes don't count, alright?

413
00:27:49,290 --> 00:27:52,870
How do you know he was my ex last time?

414
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:57,520
Someone was slacking off at work,

415
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:58,830
cleaning your picture with him.

416
00:27:58,830 --> 00:28:00,498
- After work, he picked you up with snacks.
-Stop!

417
00:28:00,498 --> 00:28:02,570
Stop!

418
00:28:03,180 --> 00:28:04,760
It's in the past now.

419
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:09,411
This time, we are really just friends.

420
00:28:09,411 --> 00:28:15,280
Do you think Yi Tian Yu
will be different this time?

421
00:28:15,280 --> 00:28:18,330
What if he's changed?

422
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:23,970
What?

423
00:28:23,970 --> 00:28:25,710
Are you jealous?

424
00:28:26,630 --> 00:28:28,130
No.

425
00:28:33,010 --> 00:28:35,380
So what if he's changed this time?

426
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:38,760
We've both gotten a second chance at life.

427
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:41,450
Why dwell on the past?

428
00:28:41,450 --> 00:28:45,680
For me, every day now feels fulfilling.

429
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:49,040
I like this feeling of living without regrets.

430
00:28:49,040 --> 00:28:51,100
This is the life I want.

431
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:52,870
Yi Tian Yu is getting better now.

432
00:28:52,870 --> 00:28:55,720
I am really happy for him.

433
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:57,800
That's all.

434
00:29:00,140 --> 00:29:01,779
Besides, he has a girlfriend now.

435
00:29:01,779 --> 00:29:03,510
They are great together.

436
00:29:03,510 --> 00:29:04,820
Don't overthink it.

437
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:06,300
Really?

438
00:29:07,630 --> 00:29:10,072
Yes!

439
00:29:10,072 --> 00:29:12,010
Can't we have a little trust between us?

440
00:29:12,010 --> 00:29:13,640
Yes.

441
00:29:19,350 --> 00:29:22,330
I heard something. Someone's outside.

442
00:29:23,340 --> 00:29:25,090
There's no sound.

443
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:27,660
No one's there, you're lying.

444
00:29:27,660 --> 00:29:29,110
Trying to trick me?

445
00:29:29,110 --> 00:29:30,280
You don't trust me?

446
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:32,050
I do.

447
00:29:32,050 --> 00:29:34,790
But you, little fox, are too cunning.

448
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:41,025
 
Mr. Lin, your competitor B&amp;C Motors announced a complete withdrawal

449
00:29:41,025 --> 00:29:42,900
of their autonomous vehicle line
from the global market.

450
00:29:42,900 --> 00:29:44,555
What's your take on that?

451
00:29:44,555 --> 00:29:47,420
I've never really seen them as "competitors".

452
00:29:47,420 --> 00:29:48,550
The market makes its choice.

453
00:29:48,550 --> 00:29:49,870
The fittest survives.

454
00:29:49,870 --> 00:29:53,900
With B&amp;C's era ending, another brand will rise
to replace it soon.

455
00:29:53,900 --> 00:29:55,480
And hopefully, they'll set a new, healthy standard

456
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:57,010
for competition in our industry.

457
00:29:57,010 --> 00:30:00,550
Six years ago, you sold your C1
autonomous driving tech to B&amp;C Motors.

458
00:30:00,550 --> 00:30:02,050
Did you foresee that one day,

459
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:04,860
C1 would be completely outmatched by C2?

460
00:30:04,860 --> 00:30:06,680
The new replaces the old.

461
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:08,290
It's how the market works.

462
00:30:08,290 --> 00:30:10,100
Some companies cut corners,

463
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:11,770
hoping to milk one technology forever.

464
00:30:11,770 --> 00:30:13,780
That's impossible.

465
00:30:13,780 --> 00:30:16,401
In the end, good money drives out bad.

466
00:30:16,401 --> 00:30:19,396
That's something our company
always reminds itself of.

467
00:30:19,396 --> 00:30:21,820
Okay, thank you.
Thank you for taking my interview.

468
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,710
Thank you too.

469
00:30:24,870 --> 00:30:27,010
Gu Xue Jiao, aren't you just generous?

470
00:30:27,010 --> 00:30:29,237
Applying to make the V2X protocol public.

471
00:30:29,237 --> 00:30:30,680
Do you know how much profit

472
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:33,020
the licensing fees for just the protocol
could bring to the company?

473
00:30:33,020 --> 00:30:35,132
If everyone's year-end bonus gets cut,
are you gonna cover that?

474
00:30:35,132 --> 00:30:38,660
Our private protocol is the most advanced
for the next few years.

475
00:30:38,660 --> 00:30:41,790
By granting free licenses to other manufacturers to produce protocol chips,

476
00:30:41,790 --> 00:30:44,760
we can actually expand Huachuang's
market influence and share.

477
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:47,590
Can you stop focusing on your own little patch?

478
00:30:47,590 --> 00:30:49,290
- My patch?
- Stick to the facts.

479
00:30:49,290 --> 00:30:51,360
It's 2024...

480
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:55,420
Zhi Hua, where are you going?

481
00:30:55,420 --> 00:30:58,540
Project lead at Blue Mountain Capital, Jason Yi, is arriving in Jinghai today.

482
00:30:58,540 --> 00:31:00,820
I've arranged a business lunch to welcome him.

483
00:31:00,820 --> 00:31:02,440
Let Gao handle the reception.

484
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:06,270
Zhi Hua, aren't you meeting
this important guest yourself?

485
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,640
I have more important matters.

486
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:20,090
Well, this view is nice.

487
00:31:21,070 --> 00:31:22,700
Beautiful.

488
00:31:29,940 --> 00:31:33,740
Honey, pour some tea for our future in-laws.

489
00:31:34,402 --> 00:31:38,630
Right! Here, have some tea.

490
00:31:38,630 --> 00:31:40,240
Look at them.

491
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:42,904
What a harmonious couple.

492
00:31:42,904 --> 00:31:44,420
Good.

493
00:31:44,420 --> 00:31:48,900
Our family doesn't have much,
just a harmonious home.

494
00:31:49,870 --> 00:31:54,200
Mutual respect has become
a family tradition for us.

495
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:55,440
How wonderful.

496
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:59,940
No wonder they say parents
are a reflection of their children's future.

497
00:31:59,940 --> 00:32:02,420
You two are such excellent parents.

498
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:04,920
That's how you raise an outstanding kid like Lin.

499
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,420
Yes.

500
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:11,260
Yes... Yes, you're right.

501
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:18,040
I wonder where those two kids are now.

502
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,050
They haven't called either.

503
00:32:19,050 --> 00:32:21,090
- Wait a bit longer.
- Okay...

504
00:32:22,550 --> 00:32:24,680
Take your time.

505
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:27,310
I've already picked some gifts.

506
00:32:27,310 --> 00:32:29,050
I'm waiting for you.

507
00:32:29,050 --> 00:32:31,040
Okay, I'll be there soon.

508
00:32:31,040 --> 00:32:33,070
But what do your parents actually like?

509
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:36,195
When I get there, let's pick something good.

510
00:32:36,195 --> 00:32:37,820
Why are you so nervous?

511
00:32:37,820 --> 00:32:39,530
It's not your first time meeting my parents.

512
00:32:39,530 --> 00:32:41,180
This time's different.

513
00:32:41,180 --> 00:32:42,250
Don't worry.

514
00:32:42,250 --> 00:32:43,940
My parents are really nice.

515
00:32:43,940 --> 00:32:48,090
They'll make your folks feel right at home.

516
00:32:49,420 --> 00:32:51,100
That's exactly what I'm worried about.

517
00:32:51,100 --> 00:32:53,204
Now, I'm looking at two key chains.

518
00:32:53,204 --> 00:32:54,690
I like them both.

519
00:32:54,690 --> 00:32:56,830
Which one do you think I should pick?

520
00:32:56,830 --> 00:32:58,610
Just buy both.

521
00:33:00,900 --> 00:33:02,570
Yi Tian Yu?

522
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,140
Isn't it funny?

523
00:33:11,140 --> 00:33:14,270
The lunch your company arranged for me is also in this mall.

524
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,590
Jason Yi?

525
00:33:17,590 --> 00:33:20,628
You're with Blue Mountain Capital?

526
00:33:20,628 --> 00:33:23,950
What? Do we only talk about work now?

527
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:26,480
Isn't that why you came back?

528
00:33:26,480 --> 00:33:28,240
There are more important things.

529
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:31,610
Like... Relationships.

530
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:36,192
You and your girlfriend are getting married?

531
00:33:36,192 --> 00:33:38,980
- Congrats.
- How about these?

532
00:33:40,290 --> 00:33:42,180
That depends on your girlfriend.

533
00:33:42,180 --> 00:33:44,160
Not up to me.

534
00:33:45,390 --> 00:33:47,230
Do you like it?

535
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:51,820
Welcome.

536
00:34:04,730 --> 00:34:06,110
Lin.

537
00:34:06,110 --> 00:34:08,260
Is that bouquet for me?

538
00:34:12,694 --> 00:34:14,304
Mr. Yi.

539
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:19,320
It's actually for my future mother-in-law.

540
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,380
You'd better hurry.

541
00:34:20,380 --> 00:34:22,220
Looks like these flowers are wilting.

542
00:34:22,220 --> 00:34:23,570
We're meeting soon.

543
00:34:23,570 --> 00:34:25,070
I'll make it.

544
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:28,720
You picked the gifts for my parents?

545
00:34:29,740 --> 00:34:31,500
I'll take them.

546
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:36,010
We're leaving now. See you.

547
00:34:36,010 --> 00:34:39,950
Neither of you two top execs is gonna have lunch with your investor?

548
00:34:39,950 --> 00:34:44,400
Is a business lunch more important than meeting our parents?

549
00:34:45,150 --> 00:34:46,920
- Let's go.
- We're off.

550
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:49,020
Say hi to Uncle and Auntie for me.

551
00:34:50,550 --> 00:34:52,130
Will do.

552
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,920
Be there soon.

553
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:01,150
They're already on their way.

554
00:35:01,150 --> 00:35:04,320
- Almost here.
- These two kids are always so busy.

555
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:06,951
They finally found time for this lunch.

556
00:35:06,951 --> 00:35:09,550
Our two families can finally meet.

557
00:35:09,550 --> 00:35:12,550
They're usually so busy. We don't even see them.

558
00:35:12,550 --> 00:35:13,592
A perfect match.

559
00:35:13,592 --> 00:35:15,323
Two workaholics.

560
00:35:15,323 --> 00:35:17,513
- Yes...
- Right...

561
00:35:20,720 --> 00:35:23,190
Sorry, I gotta take this call.

562
00:35:23,190 --> 00:35:25,050
- Go on.
- Go ahead.

563
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:29,530
Actually, our Petal takes after his Dad.

564
00:35:29,530 --> 00:35:31,490
Just loves to work.

565
00:35:31,490 --> 00:35:33,470
Yeah...

566
00:35:35,940 --> 00:35:38,110
Of course, he takes after me too.

567
00:35:38,110 --> 00:35:39,830
Excuse me.

568
00:35:41,070 --> 00:35:42,490
Okay...

569
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:45,800
Look at them.

570
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:47,610
Balancing career and life perfectly.

571
00:35:47,610 --> 00:35:49,360
Doing great on both fronts.

572
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:51,732
Compared to them, we are just...

573
00:35:51,732 --> 00:35:53,320
We're okay....

574
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:55,530
But our career...

575
00:35:56,270 --> 00:35:58,280
I have a call too.

576
00:35:59,150 --> 00:36:00,380
Why are you calling me?

577
00:36:00,380 --> 00:36:04,480
Ms. Li, could you spare some time
to discuss our dinner menu?

578
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:05,710
Stop it.

579
00:36:05,710 --> 00:36:07,880
They'll laugh at us.

580
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:09,400
The phone's been silent forever.

581
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:11,230
It's awkward.

582
00:36:11,230 --> 00:36:13,420
Okay, I got it.

583
00:36:13,420 --> 00:36:15,070
Just leave it.

584
00:36:22,230 --> 00:36:24,970
Why did you veto everything again?

585
00:36:24,970 --> 00:36:26,650
I haven't even accused you yet,

586
00:36:26,650 --> 00:36:28,050
and you're coming at me first?

587
00:36:28,050 --> 00:36:30,550
I've been in charge of this Shen City project,

588
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:32,196
and now you're kicking my people out?

589
00:36:32,196 --> 00:36:33,320
What does that mean?

590
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:34,530
It's not your first time!

591
00:36:34,530 --> 00:36:35,740
Can you keep your voice down?

592
00:36:35,740 --> 00:36:37,820
Aren't you afraid they might hear?

593
00:36:39,340 --> 00:36:41,395
I should be the one saying that.

594
00:36:41,395 --> 00:36:46,205
Tell me, are you the one
who leaked our divorce news?

595
00:36:49,646 --> 00:36:53,060
Do you know how much I spent on PR to keep this under wraps?

596
00:36:53,060 --> 00:36:54,900
Why are you always like this?

597
00:36:54,900 --> 00:36:56,760
Why can't you just shut your...

598
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,410
Stop!

599
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,650
Quit acting.

600
00:37:02,650 --> 00:37:04,160
Just stop.

601
00:37:04,160 --> 00:37:07,351
You think they can't see how demanding you are?

602
00:37:07,351 --> 00:37:10,622
You kicked me a few times while we were in there.

603
00:37:10,622 --> 00:37:15,090
I'm telling you, I've put up
with you more than enough!

604
00:37:15,090 --> 00:37:16,440
My phone. Who could it be?

605
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:17,600
Hello?

606
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:20,400
I'm not buying any house, and I don't want a loan.

607
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,570
Hello? Where is this house at?

608
00:37:22,570 --> 00:37:24,110
Future in-laws.

609
00:37:24,110 --> 00:37:26,270
Sorry. Five minutes.

610
00:37:26,270 --> 00:37:27,900
- It's alright.
- Gotta handle some family stuff.

611
00:37:27,900 --> 00:37:30,110
I have something too.

612
00:37:30,110 --> 00:37:31,570
Don't touch me.

613
00:37:31,570 --> 00:37:32,940
Talk nicely.

614
00:37:32,940 --> 00:37:34,670
Take your time.

615
00:37:37,340 --> 00:37:38,920
Good thing the call came through.

616
00:37:38,920 --> 00:37:40,415
Aren't you tired of this yet?

617
00:37:40,415 --> 00:37:41,260
What's going on?

618
00:37:41,260 --> 00:37:43,185
Lin Wen Bin! What did I tell you?

619
00:37:43,185 --> 00:37:45,700
Have you ever done anything properly?

620
00:37:45,700 --> 00:37:48,692
I told you this is very important!

621
00:37:48,692 --> 00:37:50,150
Don't mess it up.

622
00:37:50,150 --> 00:37:52,340
I think you just love to act, to pretend.

623
00:37:52,340 --> 00:37:53,870
When will this come to an end?

624
00:37:53,870 --> 00:37:55,720
This time, you lied to Xue Jiao's family.

625
00:37:55,720 --> 00:37:56,680
I can't open it.

626
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:59,670
But in the end, you'll be exposed anyway.

627
00:37:59,670 --> 00:38:00,700
I'll be exposed?

628
00:38:00,700 --> 00:38:04,800
I'm telling you. As long as
you're out of my sight, I'm super happy!

629
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:06,110
You think I wanna see you?

630
00:38:06,110 --> 00:38:07,670
Wait... I'll get the waiter.

631
00:38:07,670 --> 00:38:09,500
Waiter! Waiter!

632
00:38:09,500 --> 00:38:10,630
Help us.

633
00:38:10,630 --> 00:38:12,630
What's going on? Are you meeting in-laws?

634
00:38:12,630 --> 00:38:14,010
Why are you fighting?

635
00:38:14,010 --> 00:38:15,780
Asked for too much dowry?

636
00:38:15,780 --> 00:38:17,650
The key... You got the key?

637
00:38:17,650 --> 00:38:19,230
It's locked. The key.

638
00:38:19,230 --> 00:38:21,245
Go grab the key.

639
00:38:21,245 --> 00:38:22,576
What... Look at this.

640
00:38:22,576 --> 00:38:24,352
- They're fighting one-on-one?
- Yeah...

641
00:38:24,352 --> 00:38:26,910
What should we do?

642
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:30,320
- Dad, Mom.
- Uncle, Auntie.

643
00:38:30,320 --> 00:38:33,570
- Just in time!
- Xue Jiao, you're here!

644
00:38:33,570 --> 00:38:35,440
Uncle?

645
00:38:35,440 --> 00:38:36,630
Xue Jiao?

646
00:38:36,630 --> 00:38:38,520
Wait, they're fighting in here.

647
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:40,172
- Open the door, quick!
- I...

648
00:38:40,172 --> 00:38:42,320
- Quick, the key!
- They're fighting, quick!

649
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,440
Who are fighting?

650
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:45,230
His parents.

651
00:38:45,230 --> 00:38:46,220
Mom, Dad, don't worry.

652
00:38:46,220 --> 00:38:47,360
I know their situation.

653
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,178
- Let's go in.
- Okay...

654
00:38:48,178 --> 00:38:51,040
- Dad! Mom!
- I'm telling you...

655
00:38:51,040 --> 00:38:52,940
Please calm down.

656
00:38:52,940 --> 00:38:54,670
Why fight with your spouse?

657
00:38:54,670 --> 00:38:56,820
- I'm not his wife!
- I'm not her husband!

658
00:39:01,150 --> 00:39:03,070
So you're divorced.

659
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:06,420
Look... Did you know about this?

660
00:39:06,420 --> 00:39:09,660
- Did you know?
- I... Do I?

661
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:14,090
It's alright.

662
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:17,880
Come. Does it have to be now?

663
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:19,050
Does it have to be here?

664
00:39:19,050 --> 00:39:20,924
Your Mom's acting up regardless of the situation.

665
00:39:20,924 --> 00:39:22,900
Am I? I'm acting up?

666
00:39:22,900 --> 00:39:24,163
Look. Look at her now.

667
00:39:24,163 --> 00:39:26,370
You two said it at the same time. I heard you.

668
00:39:28,150 --> 00:39:32,540
Son, do you know who came to our restaurant today?

669
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:44,891
Future in-laws, I'm so sorry.

670
00:39:44,891 --> 00:39:46,692
-It's nothing...
- Yeah...

671
00:39:46,692 --> 00:39:49,400
- Is this bouquet from Petal?
- Yes.

672
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:51,360
- Yeah!
- Quick, give it to Auntie Li.

673
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:53,570
So our kids' marriage is settled then.

674
00:39:53,570 --> 00:39:56,220
No. Don't. We can't take it.

675
00:39:56,220 --> 00:39:58,400
What do you mean "can't take it", Dad?

676
00:39:58,400 --> 00:40:00,055
- What are you saying?
- We can take it.

677
00:40:00,055 --> 00:40:01,585
Stop talking.

678
00:40:02,507 --> 00:40:03,610
Isn't this great?

679
00:40:03,610 --> 00:40:05,840
Harmony brings wealth, right?

680
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:08,551
Seeing you all so happy now,
I'm in a good mood too.

681
00:40:08,551 --> 00:40:10,490
Guests come first.

682
00:40:10,490 --> 00:40:12,380
Today, your meal's on me.

683
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:14,235
Forget about all this.
I'll get someone to clean up later.

684
00:40:14,235 --> 00:40:15,450
I'll make sure you're taken care of.

685
00:40:15,450 --> 00:40:17,360
Wait a moment. Take a seat.

686
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:19,850
- Thank you.
- It's alright.

687
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:29,780
Weren't you two pretty good
at acting in front of me?

688
00:40:29,780 --> 00:40:32,170
Why did you lose your cool this time?

689
00:40:35,590 --> 00:40:37,740
That was all your Dad's idea.

690
00:40:37,740 --> 00:40:39,300
We were hiding it pretty well.

691
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:42,400
Nothing about stock shake-ups or info leaks.

692
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:46,190
Then out of nowhere,
he just couldn't hide it anymore.

693
00:40:46,190 --> 00:40:49,530
I clearly said we should be
honest with our future in-laws.

694
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:51,380
Why can't we just be honest?

695
00:40:51,380 --> 00:40:53,090
It was your dumb idea.

696
00:40:53,090 --> 00:40:54,220
How old are you?

697
00:40:54,220 --> 00:40:55,610
Think before you speak!

698
00:40:55,610 --> 00:40:56,860
Honesty?

699
00:40:56,860 --> 00:40:58,800
It'll just drive our in-laws away!

700
00:40:58,800 --> 00:41:00,780
- Seriously...
- You're right.

701
00:41:00,780 --> 00:41:02,360
You're right, okay? You're always right.

702
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:04,230
Always the right one.

703
00:41:20,341 --> 00:41:21,760
Son.

704
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:23,400
Son.

